Write a program that takes two integer inputs from the user and performs division.
Implement try-catch to handle the ArithmeticException (or equivalent) that occurs when the denominator is zero.



OUTPUT:-
Enter the dividend: 10
Enter the divisor: 0
Can not divide by 0!

Enter the dividend: 10
Enter the divisor: 5
After division: 2



import java.util.*;

public class App{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter the dividend: ");
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter the divisor: ");
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int res;

        try{
            res = a/b;
            System.out.println("After division: "+res);
        }
        catch(ArithmeticException e){
            System.out.println("Can not divide by 0!");
        }
    }
}
